<!--Ozaho no Ōkimi--><!--Ozaho no Ōkimi--><!--Ozaho no Ōkimi--><!--Ozaho no Ōkimi--><!--Ozaho no Ōkimi--><!--Ozaho no Ōkimi--><!--Ozaho no Ōkimi--><!--Ozaho no Ōkimi--><!--Ozaho no Ōkimi-->

'''Ozaho no Ōkimi''' (袁邪本王, dates unknown) was a {{ill|Japanese Imperial family|ja|皇族|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} figure of the {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Overview ==
Ozaho no Ōkimi is enshrined alongside his father, {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, as a deity at the {{ill|Karuno Shrine|ja|軽野神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Aichigun, Shiga|ja|愛知郡 (滋賀県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Shiga Prefecture. He is also worshipped at the {{ill|Sawaka Shrine|ja|佐波加刀神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Nagahama|ja|長浜市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Shiga Prefecture.
=== Alternative Theory by Tsutomu Hōga ===
According to historian Tsutomu Hōga, while Ozaho's brother {{ill|Sahohiko no Ōkimi|ja|狭穂彦王|1=Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} is traditionally considered the ancestor of the {{ill|Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|甲斐国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the generational gap between Sahohiko no Ōkimi (active during the {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} era) and the first Kai no Kuni no Miyatsuko, {{ill|Shioumi Atane|ja|塩海足尼|1=Shiomi no Sukune|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, who served during the {{ill|Emperor Keikō|ja|景行天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} era, makes this connection problematic. Hōga proposes that Ozaho no Ōkimi was another name for {{ill|Tomochitsuhiko no Mikoto|ja|臣知津彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, identified as the father of Shioumi Atane.<ref>Tsutomu Hōga, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/keihu/kaikokuso/kaikok1.htm Genealogy of Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko]," ''Kojiki-no-Heika Room'', 2016.</ref>
== Genealogy ==
Ozaho no Ōkimi was the son of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a child of {{ill|Emperor Kaika|ja|開化天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and his consort, {{ill|Saho no Ōkuramito-me|ja|沙本之大闇見戸売|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the daughter of {{ill|Kasuga Takekunikatsutome|ja|春日建国勝戸売|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He is considered an ancestor of the {{ill|Katsuno Betsu|ja|葛野別|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Chikatsuomi Kanobetsu|ja|近淡海蚊野別|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} lineages. His siblings include: * {{ill|Sahohiko no Ōkimi|ja|狭穂彦王|1=Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the progenitor of the {{ill|Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|甲斐国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Murobiko no Ōkimi|ja|室毘古王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the progenitor of the {{ill|Wakasa Mimine Betsu|ja|若狭耳別|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Sahohime no Mikoto|ja|狭穂姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Empress of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
