Ozaho no Ōkimi is enshrined alongside his father, {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|qq=}}, as a deity at the {{ill|Karuno Shrine|ja|軽野神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karuno Shrine|qq=}} in [[:en:Echi District, Shiga|Aichigun, Shiga]], Shiga Prefecture. He is also worshipped at the {{ill|Sawaka Shrine|ja|佐波加刀神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sawaka Shrine|qq=}} in [[:en:Nagahama, Shiga|Nagahama]], Shiga Prefecture.
=== Alternative Theory by Tsutomu Hōga ===
According to historian Tsutomu Hōga, while Ozaho's brother {{ill|Sahohiko no Ōkimi|ja|狭穂彦王|1=Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sahohiko no Ōkimi|13=User:Immanuelle/Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=}} is traditionally considered the ancestor of the {{ill|Kai no Kuni no Miyatsuko|lt=Kai no Kuni no Miyatsuko|lt=Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|甲斐国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}, the generational gap between Sahohiko no Ōkimi (active during the [[:en:Emperor Suinin|Emperor Suinin]] era) and the first Kai no Kuni no Miyatsuko, {{ill|Shioumi Atane|ja|塩海足尼|1=Shiomi no Sukune|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shioumi Atane|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiomi no Sukune|qq=}}, who served during the [[:en:Emperor Keikō|Emperor Keikō]] era, makes this connection problematic. Hōga proposes that Ozaho no Ōkimi was another name for {{ill|Tomochitsuhiko no Mikoto|ja|臣知津彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomochitsuhiko no Mikoto|qq=}}, identified as the father of Shioumi Atane.<ref>Tsutomu Hōga, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/keihu/kaikokuso/kaikok1.htm Genealogy of Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko]," ''Kojiki-no-Heika Room'', 2016.</ref>
