{{Infobox person|gender={{ill|male|qid=Q6581097}}|father={{ill|Hikoimasu|qid=Q11487910}}|mother={{ill|Q13360104|qid=Q13360104}}|relatives={{ill|Empress Sahohime|qid=Q11571754}}; {{ill|Prince Sahohiko|qid=Q11571755}}; {{ill|Tanba no Michinushi|qid=Q11368587}}; {{ill|Yamashiro-no-Otsutsukimawaka|qid=Q11466268}}}}{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11626514]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 08:52, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Ozaho no Ōkimi''' (袁邪本王, dates unknown) was a {{ill|Japanese Imperial family|ja|皇族|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Imperial family|qq=|1=Imperial Family of Japan|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11581068}} figure of the [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]].
== Overview ==
Ozaho no Ōkimi is enshrined alongside his father, {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|qq=}}, as a deity at the {{ill|Karuno Shrine|ja|軽野神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karuno Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in [[:en:Echi District, Shiga|Aichigun, Shiga]], Shiga Prefecture. He is also worshipped at the {{ill|Sawaka Shrine|ja|佐波加刀神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sawaka Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in [[:en:Nagahama, Shiga|Nagahama]], Shiga Prefecture.
=== Alternative Theory by Tsutomu Hōga ===
According to historian Tsutomu Hōga, while Ozaho's brother {{ill|Sahohiko no Ōkimi|ja|狭穂彦王|1=Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sahohiko no Ōkimi|13=User:Immanuelle/Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=}} is traditionally considered the ancestor of the {{ill|Kai no Kuni no Miyatsuko|lt=Kai no Kuni no Miyatsuko|lt=Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|甲斐国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}, the generational gap between Sahohiko no Ōkimi (active during the [[:en:Emperor Suinin|Emperor Suinin]] era) and the first Kai no Kuni no Miyatsuko, {{ill|Shioumi Atane|ja|塩海足尼|1=Shiomi no Sukune|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shioumi Atane|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiomi no Sukune|qq=}}, who served during the [[:en:Emperor Keikō|Emperor Keikō]] era, makes this connection problematic. Hōga proposes that Ozaho no Ōkimi was another name for {{ill|Tomochitsuhiko no Mikoto|ja|臣知津彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomochitsuhiko no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, identified as the father of Shioumi Atane.<ref>Tsutomu Hōga, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/keihu/kaikokuso/kaikok1.htm Genealogy of Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko]," ''Kojiki-no-Heika Room'', 2016.</ref>
== Genealogy ==
Ozaho no Ōkimi was the son of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|qq=}}, a child of [[:en:Emperor Kaika|Emperor Kaika]], and his consort, {{ill|Saho no Ōkuramito-me|ja|沙本之大闇見戸売|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saho no Ōkuramito-me|qq=}}, the daughter of {{ill|Kasuga Takekunikatsutome|ja|春日建国勝戸売|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kasuga Takekunikatsutome|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. He is considered an ancestor of the {{ill|Katsuno Betsu|ja|葛野別|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuno Betsu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and {{ill|Chikatsuomi Kanobetsu|ja|近淡海蚊野別|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikatsuomi Kanobetsu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} lineages. His siblings include: * {{ill|Sahohiko no Ōkimi|ja|狭穂彦王|1=Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sahohiko no Ōkimi|13=User:Immanuelle/Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=}}, the progenitor of the {{ill|Kai no Kuni no Miyatsuko|lt=Kai no Kuni no Miyatsuko|lt=Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|甲斐国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kai Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}. * {{ill|Murobiko no Ōkimi|ja|室毘古王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murobiko no Ōkimi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, the progenitor of the {{ill|Wakasa Mimine Betsu|ja|若狭耳別|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakasa Mimine Betsu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. * [[:en:Saho-hime|Sahohime no Mikoto]], Empress of [[:en:Emperor Suinin|Emperor Suinin]].
